# 📝 Homework

To strengthen our understanding of the **Model-View-Controller (MVC)** architecture, we were assigned to design real-world applications by identifying their **Model**, **View**, and **Controller** components.

I worked on three practical use cases:

### 🤖 Personal AI Agent

Designed a personal AI assistant capable of managing user information, daily tasks, reminders, and personalized solutions while maintaining user privacy.

### 🏭 Pumps Factory Management System

Applied the MVC architecture to an industrial environment by separating customer records, product information, machine details, and engineering calculations into well-defined components.

### 🤝 Buddy Finder

Designed a social matching application where user profiles, common interests, and AI-powered recommendation logic work together to connect like-minded individuals.

This assignment showed me that MVC is not just a theoretical concept—it is a practical framework that can be applied to almost any software application.

